			<div class="question">Question 2: How to prepare for the companies of that sector?</div>

			<div class="answer">Answer:The first most important thing is to know your syllabus, some of the concepts asked during interviews were absent in our curriculum, so we had to collect those resources from our seniors. So, knowing your syllabus and collecting the required resources must be the first step. I know it is a vast syllabus but 6-7 months of consistent effort shall be enough to get prepared. 
			Begin slowly and configure your approach as you complete one part and move on to the next. Solving GATE Questions is really important because to score high in the written test, one must be quick enough to answer the MCQs due to the limited time and since most of the questions are similar to GATE questions, it really helps.
			The best tip is to be consistent while preparing for core companies. Some topics fade away very quickly and revision should be of utmost priority. Some of the important topics are Digital Electronics, C, Verilog, Analog Electronics, Rabaey Book Chapters 3,5,6 – very important, VLSI Design, STA, DFT, Computer Architecture, Transient Analysis, etc.
			I have tried to be very brief about the topics here because even if one gives me an hour to speak on this in detail, it will not be sufficient and I am sure most of you already know about the syllabus but if you still have any doubts related to the syllabus or preparation, please feel free to contact me, I will be happy to help.
			</div>
