			<div class="question">Question 7:Any extra advice to your juniors for technical skills that they should develop?</div>

			<div class="answer">Answer: Technical skills like Digital VLSI Design, Verilog and C are really important. Questions in interviews and written test will definitely be asked from these topics irrespective of the company you apply. CGPA is also important but anything above 8-8.2 will be good enough to get shortlisted, what matters is giving your 100% in the written test and technical interview because that will boost your chances. Focus on your CGPA, try to score as much as you can in the written test, be thorough with the basics and some concepts which are not part of the curriculum, and then you will surely get selected somewhere – All the best!!</div>
